'''十月惊奇'''<ref>{{cite web |last1=Tang |first1=Shuhua |title=October Surprises：美国选举中的“十月惊奇” |url=https://cn.nytimes.com/culture/20181106/wod-october-surprises/ |website=纽约时报中文网 |publisher=[[纽约时报|纽约时报]] |accessdate=2020-11-07 |language=zh-hans |date=2018-11-06 |archive-date=2020-08-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200805194714/https://cn.nytimes.com/culture/20181106/wod-october-surprises/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>（{{lang-en|October Surprise}}）是一个美国政治术语，指美国在11月选举前发生、可能对大选结果产生影响的新闻事件。这些新闻事件可能是蓄谋已久，也可能是突然发生。由于[[选举日_(美国)|美国选举日]]总是安排在11月上旬，10月发生的事件最有可能左右投票者的意向。<ref name="Politico">{{cite news|url=https://www.politico.com/magazine/story/2016/10/october-surprises-214320|title=15 October Surprises That Wreaked Havoc on Politics|first=Taylor|last=Gee|work=[[政客_(杂志)|政客]]|date=2016-10-04|accessdate=2020-07-16|archive-date=2020-11-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201126220216/https://www.politico.com/magazine/story/2016/10/october-surprises-214320|dead-url=no}}</ref>该词汇由[[罗纳德·里根|罗纳德·里根]]的{{tsl|en|campaign manager|竞选经理}}[[威廉·约瑟夫·卡西|威廉·约瑟夫·卡西]]在1980年发明。<ref name="Smithsonian">{{cite web|url=https://www.smithsonianmag.com/history/strange-history-october-surprise-180960741/|title=The Strange History of the October Surprise|first=Jared|last=Keller|work=[[Smithsonian_(magazine)|Smithsonian]]|date=2016-10-11|accessdate=2020-07-16|archive-date=2020-09-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200907205233/https://www.smithsonianmag.com/history/strange-history-october-surprise-180960741/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

